    public static class Int2ShortMaps.EmptyMap
extends Int2ShortFunctions.EmptyFunction
implements Int2ShortMap, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
    An immutable class representing an empty type-specific map.

    This class may be useful to implement your own in case you subclass a type-specific map.

      • int2ShortEntrySet

        public ObjectSet<Int2ShortMap.Entry> int2ShortEntrySet()
        Description copied from interface: Int2ShortMap
        Returns a type-specific set view of the mappings contained in this map.

        This method is necessary because there is no inheritance along type parameters: it is thus impossible to strengthen Int2ShortMap.entrySet() so that it returns an ObjectSet of type-specific entries (the latter makes it possible to access keys and values with type-specific methods).

        Specified by:
        int2ShortEntrySet in interface Int2ShortMap
        Returns:
        a type-specific set view of the mappings contained in this map.
